text: Activation of the human immunodeficiency virus type 1 enhancer is not dependent on <extra_id_0> NFAT-1 <extra_id_2> Protein <extra_id_1> .
The function of a putative <extra_id_0> NFAT-1 <extra_id_2> Protein <extra_id_1> site in the human immunodeficiency virus type 1 enhancer has been analyzed .
Activation by the T-cell antigen receptor is minimal in Jurkat cells and is mediated by the kappa B sites .

The putative <extra_id_0> NFAT-1 <extra_id_2> Protein <extra_id_1> region is not required for the response to anti-CD3 or to mitogens in T-cell , B-cell , or monocyte / macrophage leukemia lines , nor is it a cis - acting negative regulatory element .
